courses.learning_outcomes:
Upon completion of this course, students should be able to:

1. Increase the understanding of Dunhuang Buddhist iconography correctly, strengthen the ability to appreciate Dunhuang Buddhist iconography;
2. Increase the understanding of Buddhist doctrine correctly, apply Buddhist teaching into daily life, and strengthen the ability of problem solving;
3. Strengthen the skill of individual & group learning, writing and presentation.

Upon completion of the subject, students will be able to:

1. understand fundamental Buddhist teachings;
2. read Buddhist studies written in English and become familiar with current English scholarship on Buddhism;
3. read Buddhist primary sources in classic Chinese;
4. understand and critically review the methodology, research questions, and interdisciplinary tendencies in Buddhist studies;
5. learn how to conduct and present academic research using both primary and secondary sources.
